      {
        "item": "Oncological Emergencies",
        "notes_updates": "SUB-PROTOCOL: Tumour Lysis Syndrome | Pathophysiology: Massive tumour cell lysis - release of tumour cell contents into circulation causing electrolyte derangement (low Ca2+, high K+, high PO4, high uric acid), renal failure, metabolic acidosis, seizures, cardiac arrhythmias | Triggers: Chemotherapy, Radiotherapy, High dose steroids, Hormonal therapy, Surgery, Rapidly growing tumour | Risk factors: Leukaemia, Lymphoma, Aggressive treatment, High tumour burden | Diagnostic criteria: Cairo-Bishop criteria | Management: Monitored bed | Aggressive IV fluids (balanced crystalloid) - aim urine output >2ml/kg/hr | If volume overloaded: Lasix | Manage electrolyte abnormalities (hyperkalaemia, hyperphosphataemia, hypocalcaemia) | Supportive treatment | Dialysis indications: oliguria, anuria, volume overload, persistent hyperkalaemia, hyperphosphataemia-induced symptomatic hypocalcaemia | Disposition: Urgent Oncology referral. ICU referral for severe cases | | SUB-PROTOCOL: Febrile Neutropenia | Definition: Fever + neutropenia (ANC <1000/microlitre). Fever: single oral temp >38.3C or >38C for >1 hour | Often 5-10 days after last chemotherapy | Management: Rapid work-up and empiric antibiotics | Look carefully for signs of infection but defer PR (typhlitis) | Look everywhere: skin, mucous membranes, peri-anal, indwelling lines/catheters | Consider typhlitis: necrotising enterocolitis, appendicitis mimic - CT Abdo, NGT, NPO, IV fluid | Send appropriate samples (blood cultures, urine culture, etc.) | Early antibiotics: Tazocin adequate broad spectrum | Consider fungal cover | Differential: Drug reaction, PE, other oncological emergency | Disposition: Early oncology referral | | SUB-PROTOCOL: Superior Vena Cava (SVC) Syndrome | Pathophysiology: Mechanical obstruction of SVC. Internal: clot. External: tumour/lymph node | Cancers: Lung, NHL Lymphoma | Symptoms: Dyspnoea, Facial oedema, Cough, Chest pain, Dysphagia, Distended neck veins, Facial plethora, Ar